    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>TIKVAH</h1><p>1. Harhas’s son, father of Shallum, and the father-in-law of Huldah the prophetess (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs22:14\">2&nbsp;Kgs 22:14</a>); alternately called Tokhath (kjv “Tikvath”) in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:22\">2&nbsp;Chronicles 34:22</a>.</p><p>2. Father of Jahzeiah, who was one of the four individuals on record who opposed Ezra’s command to divorce foreign wives (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:15\">Ezr 10:15</a>).</p>",
